cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses an information-theoretic approach to quantify the potential latency reduction in a Fog-RAN with D2D communication. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies a Fog-RAN with cache-enabled Edge Nodes and dedicated fronthaul connections, and proposes joint caching, transmission, and D2D communication policies. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a Fog-RAN system with multiple components (caching, transmission, D2D communication) and aims to minimize the Normalized Delivery Time metric. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed approach to content delivery in a Fog-RAN with D2D communication. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with content delivery to mobile users, which is a multimedia application.
